-- Liverpool Signs Defender Daniel Agger to New Long-Term Contract
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-10-05T14:12:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-05/liverpool-signs-defender-daniel-agger-to-new-long-term-contract.html
Liverpool signed defender Daniel
Agger to a new contract, the Premier League club said on its
website.  Agger, 27 has appeared in 177 games since joining the Reds
from Brondby in his native Denmark in January 2006. He’s scored
nine goals.  “I want to be a a part of this club in the future,” Agger
said on Liverpool’s website. “I feel I belong here and as long
as the manager and the owners want me, I’ll be here.”  Liverpool didn’t disclose length of the agreement, only
saying that it was “long term.”  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  